olive oil
1 stalk celery
1 Brown Onion
3 clove garlic
1 carrot
2 packet portabello mushrooms
1 packet beef & pork mince
1 sachet Aussie Spice Blend
1 packet tomato paste
½ cup water
1 bag baby spinach leaves
1 packet Grated Parmesan Cheese
30 g butter
1 packet filo pastry

• Preheat oven to 220ºC/200ºC fan-forced.
• Finely chop celery, onion and garlic. Grate the
carrot. Thinly slice portabello mushrooms.

• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive
oil over high heat. Cook beef & pork mince,
breaking up with a spoon, until just browned,
3-4 minutes.
• Add mushrooms and cook until just softened,
3-4 minutes.
• Add celery, onion and carrot and cook, stirring,
until softened, 4-6 minutes.

• Add garlic and Aussie spice blend and cook,
stirring, until fragrant, 1-2 minutes.
• Reduce heat to medium, then add tomato paste
and the water and cook, stirring, until slightly
reduced, 1-2 minutes.
• Stir through baby spinach leaves until wilted,
1 minute. Season to taste.

TIP: Add a dash more water if the mince is dry!

• Transfer mince mixture to a baking dish, then
sprinkle over grated Parmesan cheese.

Little cooks: Add the magic touch by sprinkling the
cheese on top.

• Add the butter to a small heatproof bowl and
microwave in 10 second bursts until melted.
• Lightly scrunch each sheet of filo pastry and
place on top of mince mixture to completely
cover.
• Gently brush melted butter over to coat.
Bake pie until golden, 15-20 minutes.

Little cooks: Kids can help with scrunching the filo
pastry!

• Divide homestyle beef, pork and mushroom filo
pie between plates. Enjoy!